pets <- read_csv("data/pets.csv")

Delimiter: ","
chr (3): name, animal, sex
dbl (3): age, weight, sleep

#colour palettes

pets %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = age,
             y = weight,
             colour = sleep))+
  geom_point()

#continuous colours - sequential and diverging #sequential

pets %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = age,
             y = weight,
             colour = sleep))+
  geom_point()+
  scale_colour_gradient(low = "#ffe3e3",
                        high = "#fa0300")

#diverging

pets %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = age,
             y = weight,
             colour = sleep))+
  geom_point()+
  scale_colour_gradient2(low = "blue",
                         mid = "white",
                         high = "red",
                         midpoint = median(pets$sleep))+
  theme_bw()

#Discrete colours

students %>% 
  distinct(superpower) %>% 
  pull
[1] "Telepathy"    "Invisibility" "Fly"          "Freeze time" 
students %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = school_year,
             fill = superpower))+
  geom_bar()+
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("Fly" = "coral",
                               "Freeze time" = "seagreen",
                               "Invisibility" = "orange",
                               "Telepathy" = "red"))

pets %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = weight,
             y = age, 
             colour = sleep))+
  geom_point()+
  scale_color_distiller(palette = "RdPu")
